  <div slot="quick-answer">
    <p><strong>Quick Answer:</strong> Malbec is best with steak, grilled meat, burgers, barbecue, and other savory dishes that can absorb its dark fruit and moderate tannin. It is most useful when you want a fuller red without the stricter tannin of Cabernet Sauvignon.</p>
  </div>

